Content:

This is disc one of a 2 cd set I bought a while ago.
-In China, they often combine 2 albums into one package.
-This could be 2 albums, or 1 two-disc album.  I don&#039;t know.

Taiwanese rock and roll.  Pretty popular.  Been around a fairly long time.

It&#039;s considered to be "rock", 
-but IMHO it&#039;s stereotypical, bland Chinese rock.  
-It&#039;s not bad, but I prefer music with a little harder edge to it (or hippie noodling or booty-shaking funk).
-I figured I&#039;d put it up just in case you might like it

To be honest, I can&#039;t figure out exactly what album(s) this/these is/are.  
-I tried to find the details for you all, but in my limited searching, I couldn&#039;t.
-Song #1 has an English title, so I labeled the file appropriately.
-Song #7 has a video that I found on the internet, so I labeled that one with the Chinese title.
--You can see the video here: <a href=" http://music.sina.com.cn/yueku/v/294726.html" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://music.sina.com.cn/yueku/v/294726.html</a>
--title is:  ?????? = ni shi ni wo shi wo = You are You, I am Me

If you really want me to post the other CD, just ask, and I will.  And/Or, If you seriously need a chinese language 

track list, I suppose I could do that for you.
